                <h1>Ukraine Flag: Symbol of Freedom and Heritage</h1>
                <p>The flag of Ukraine features two horizontal stripes: a vibrant blue top half symbolizing the sky and a golden-yellow bottom half representing the wheat fields. This iconic design reflects the nation’s agricultural heritage and rich landscapes. Historically, the colors are associated with freedom, unity, and resilience.</p>
